Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.27,0:01:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,, Eyes, look your last. {from https://www.folger.edu/explore/shakespeares-works/romeo-and-juliet/read/}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.85,0:01:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Arms, take your last embrace.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.99,0:01:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And, lips, O, you\NThe doors of breath,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.21,0:01:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,seal with a righteous kiss...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.73,0:01:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.44,0:01:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A dateless bargain.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.22,0:02:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A dateless bargain to engrossing death.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.79,0:02:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm no good! \NCan I have the script for a moment?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.98,0:02:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! Come on, get a grip!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.33,0:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! You must stop dawdling and learn your lines—\Nwe’ve only ten days left until the concert!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.00,0:02:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I really...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.77,0:02:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the crucial point of the whole play!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.64,0:02:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s meant to be a heartbreaking scene of lovers dying, \Ntorn apart by a feud between their families!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.18,0:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to feel it! {lit: liven it up - think she means "make it believable"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.66,0:02:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, Madam Director.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.35,0:02:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise I'll memorize it all by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.25,0:02:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, first form? Time's up. \NPlease vacate the stage.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.29,0:02:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.39,0:02:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I really want more rehearsal time.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.99,0:02:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,True. We have to compete for the gym.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.13,0:02:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{??? ne ** nanishiyatte miyou ka = hey, I wonder what ** is doing}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.20,0:02:47.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.02,0:02:51.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's up with Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.54,0:02:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, what's the hold-up? \NLet's go have tea!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.11,0:02:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.37,0:03:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm bored.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.56,0:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The other roses are alive and well, \Nbut this one's just like me{, frfr}. {/bursting with life}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.63,0:03:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like I can do anything about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.29,0:03:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A dateless bargain to engrossing...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.97,0:03:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, why don't you stop memorizing lines \Nat least when you're having tea?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.40,0:03:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm really strapped for time.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.56,0:03:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard. \NI’m sure I’d fall flat at learning lines.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.45,0:03:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But learning the dance steps \Nis jolly hard too, isn’t it? {lit: memorizing the dance choreography}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.09,0:03:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, but at least in dance, you learn it with your body rather than your head.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.03,0:03:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I wish I had two heads sometimes.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.23,0:03:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ol' Shakespeare's lines are a pain to learn. {?? urameshi is "reproachful; hateful; bitter" - she might just be slurring urayamashi (envy), but I hear urameshi too clearly here - probably means "I hate his hard-to-read language"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.00,0:03:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.67,0:03:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, hasn't Sheila's been \Nrather gloomy lately?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.87,0:04:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila’s taking part \Nin a French play, isn’t she?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.24,0:04:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle must be working her to the bone. {lit: wringing her dry}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.48,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Abominable! That is not French.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.22,0:04:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So-so. Pat's impression was much more believable. {??? lit: 60 points - that weird point system again that I never heard of, was 25 points in one of the previous eps, 60 now so i guess it's better? maybe it really is "out of 100" after all?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.62,0:04:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's so-so?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.79,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, really? Sheila won't be \Nin the French play either?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.28,0:04:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.16,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought she was going to be \Nin Romeo and Juliet.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.93,0:04:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she not?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.87,0:04:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That's weird, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.74,0:04:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure Sheila was to play \Nthe role of Monsieur Triomphal... {?????????? no clue what's that musshu tokutoku; in the book it's never mentioned, and the play is only referred to as "french play" so it's safe to assume it's some play the students wrote themselves or some generic name of a play; as for the name of that character, tokutoku is most likely the proper name, a play on either of those meanings: https://jisho.org/search/tokutoku although could also be dokudoku = peculiarity; uniqueness; characteristic - or maybe it's not a name at all and dokudoku here means something like "the role unique to her/written by her/unique role"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that role was assigned \Nto Mary from the beginning. {this is the first name that's not actually in the book, so fingers crossed it's actually mary and not some obscure variation like the others (catherine > kathleen, bella > vera)}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.96,0:04:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness! Could it be that Sheila \Ndidn't get a role at all, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.90,0:04:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.52,0:04:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No one invited me, that's why. {lit: no voice came from anywhere}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.42,0:04:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You should've told us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.09,0:04:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just sure you were going to appear in that French play.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.79,0:04:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine, I don't have \Nany special talent for it anyway, do I?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.73,0:05:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, we never said that.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.43,0:05:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't get a role, you should've affirmed it clearly with everyone present.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.54,0:05:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a school concert that we all create together, \Nso everyone must be a part of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.48,0:05:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no crying over spilt milk, is there?! {lit: not like there's anything to be done about it now}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.91,0:05:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone has their roles assigned \Nand is already busy rehearsing.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.72,0:05:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares if I'm not a part of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.82,0:05:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, that sulky attitude \Nis almost downright foolish.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.59,0:05:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I am a fool, all right?! \NSo stop distracting me and leave me alone!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.92,0:05:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.92,0:05:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.97,0:05:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That Sheila...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.41,0:05:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why she kept quiet \Nabout it up to now?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.84,0:05:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She felt left out. {?? lit: thinking you've been ignored}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.43,0:05:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy that! \NWhat is she, a little baby? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.65,0:05:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't babysit her all the time. {?? lit: taking care of someone won't cut}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.38,0:05:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't just leave her be \Nlike this either, can we?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.42,0:05:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.37,0:05:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard, being the only one \Nwho doesn’t get to perform in the school concert.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.72,0:05:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What's that I'm hearing? \NNow you suddenly care about Sheila? {lit: protecting Sheila - as opposed to hating her before}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.66,0:06:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I do sympathize with her! {/know how she feels}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.73,0:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, I’ve also been pulled \Nfrom a lacrosse match I was meant to play in.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.60,0:06:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.70,0:06:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain made a mistake \Nand we had too many people on the field.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.77,0:06:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the whole school was buzzing with rumours about why I was pulled,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.44,0:06:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s been weighing on me a lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.04,0:06:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.48,0:06:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you two! \NI can be pretty sensitive too.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.38,0:06:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are lucky to have each other.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.05,0:06:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can talk about anything, \Nsupport one another, and comfort one another.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.42,0:06:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re like Sheila \Nand can’t share your troubles with anyone,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.96,0:06:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even the smallest thing feels like a huge deal.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.76,0:06:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But what can we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.43,0:06:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe ask Miss Kennedy \Nto include an extra role?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.24,0:06:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it. She’d struggle to memorize the lines on such short notice.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.77,0:06:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Her lines, right...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.37,0:06:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I've got an idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.26,0:06:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.11,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Prompter?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.26,0:06:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, if someone forgets a line onstage, \Nyou can prompt them by glancing at the script.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.35,0:06:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I can do that well.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.08,0:06:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.42,0:07:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Just having you watch their backs \Nwould give everyone confidence. Please. {/just you being there}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.03,0:07:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.53,0:07:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,O Romeo, Romeo, wherefore art thou Romeo?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.24,0:07:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Deny thy father and refuse thy name,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.81,0:07:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, if thou wilt not, be but sworn my love,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.78,0:07:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll no longer be a Capulet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.85,0:07:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I hear more, or shall I speak at this?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.96,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,'Tis but thy name that is my enemy.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.72,0:07:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A-And...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.06,0:07:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thou art thyself, though not a Montague...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.12,0:07:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Thou art thyself, though not a Montague.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.04,0:07:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! News! I got news!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.54,0:07:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.71,0:08:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.90,0:08:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.98,0:08:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Old Sheila is still reading the script, \Neven this hour! {meaning "she is very dedicated to it"... how is this news I fail to see}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.89,0:08:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, impressive! \NShe might just memorize it in full.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.92,0:08:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking Sheila to be a prompter \Nwas the right call.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.09,0:08:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Even if she looked disinterested at first.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.00,0:08:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila really is a sport!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.72,0:08:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was given such a boring role, \NI'd stop caring halfway through.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.02,0:08:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,True! For Pat, it'd be impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.04,0:08:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't have to say it so clearly!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.24,0:08:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,O Romeo, Romeo,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.34,0:08:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,wherefore art thou Romeo?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.48,0:08:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Deny thy father...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.15,0:08:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera sure is lucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.05,0:08:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She gets to play Juliet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.09,0:08:49.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dad,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.75,0:08:51.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mum,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.25,0:08:53.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The school concert is almost here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.70,0:08:59.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,I’ve memorized Romeo’s long speeches perfectly, \Nand our rehearsals run smoothly.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.62,0:09:02.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,The performance preparations \Nare also in full swing. {workmanship; execution; shape and quality (of an article); finishing touches}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.24,0:09:07.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,We made everything ourselves—\Nthe costumes and the props!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.17,0:09:11.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's a shame you can't see it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.72,0:09:15.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Once the school concert is over, \Nit's the long-awaited {end-of-year }holiday!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.86,0:09:21.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,We'll be bringing back lots of stories to tell, \Nso look forward to it!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.94,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Some shall be pardoned, and some punished.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.10,0:09:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For never was a story of more woe\NThan this of Juliet and her Romeo.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.67,0:09:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.82,0:09:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You've all done a wonderful job.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.39,0:09:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard to tell such a long story \Nin just two episodes.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.93,0:10:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Juliet is only fourteen in the play.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.10,0:10:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,About the same age as you. {don't remember how I concluded they were ten last time, but I suspect that the show producers didn't care much for continuity either}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.00,0:10:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you gave a convincing portrayal \Nof two young lovers’ devotion. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.64,0:10:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Miss Roberts?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.67,0:10:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.81,0:10:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For the short time you had to rehearse, \NI think it turned out really well.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.71,0:10:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui, vraiment!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.38,0:10:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll have to put in double the effort \Nif we want our French play to be just as good.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.15,0:10:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had to rate it, \NI'd give you 85 out of 100. {ye, pmuch confirms it}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.36,0:10:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll be looking forward \Nto the actual performance.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.33,0:10:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes the stage rehearsals.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.01,0:10:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.57,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.17,0:10:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my heart is racing!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.27,0:10:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our best and bring it to 100/100!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.64,0:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.08,0:10:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.82,0:10:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The performances start in only two hours!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.86,0:10:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! We'll be done soon!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.89,0:11:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All ready here, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.59,0:11:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,O Romeo, wherefore art thou Romeo?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.83,0:11:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so good at it, Vera!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.10,0:11:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep this up \Nand carry it into the real thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.37,0:11:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't accept anything \Nless, you hear?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.30,0:11:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.44,0:11:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's move the costumes now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.38,0:11:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.18,0:11:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It... hurts...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.64,0:11:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Vera?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.46,0:11:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.54,0:11:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.91,0:11:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.61,0:11:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it looks to me \Nlike you've badly hurt your ankle.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.85,0:12:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No fracture, most likely, but it’s better \Nto get an X-ray at the hospital just to be sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.25,0:12:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it, I'll call a car.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.29,0:12:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Vera?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.63,0:12:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, girls. I'm making you all worry. \NAnd the school concert...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.60,0:12:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.31,0:12:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a shame, but it doesn't seem \Nthat Vera will be able to perform.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.39,0:12:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.98,0:12:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t very well stage a play without Juliet.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.98,0:12:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.92,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll just have to give up for today \Nand try to perform it some other time.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.92,0:12:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... It was coming together so nicely...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.72,0:12:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.72,0:12:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been trying so hard to memorize my lines, \Nbut if I relax now, I’ll forget the lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.83,0:12:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d be such bad luck if we couldn’t stage the final performance after coming this far.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.66,0:12:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.40,0:12:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everything in life \Nalways goes according to plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.37,0:12:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that throw a spanner in the works \Nhappen all the time.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.72,0:12:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when your true value is put to test. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.38,0:12:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best to see if there’s a way \Nto get yourselves out of this crisis.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.15,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we try to salvage this? {???? idk what she means: why not try somehow}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.78,0:13:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! As long as you're doing your best, \Nit's okay to fail. {??? /make mistakes}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! If you just give up, \Nnothing will come out of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.22,0:13:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But who's going to play Juliet?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.59,0:13:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have her. We have a Juliet! {lit: can, she can}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.68,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.83,0:13:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a girl who can play Juliet!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.00,0:13:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.54,0:13:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who remembers all the lines \Nand movements. Right, Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.54,0:13:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.07,0:13:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.31,0:13:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right! How come it didn’t \Noccur to me right away?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.56,0:13:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What, me?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.01,0:13:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be unreasonable. \NI can't do it. I don't have the confidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.03,0:13:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes you can! \NPlease Sheila, help us out! {lit: accept [the role]}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.28,0:13:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll all be supporting you!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.88,0:13:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.02,0:13:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it, Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.47,0:13:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.16,0:13:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You ought to try.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.69,0:13:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.48,0:13:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm sure Vera would be happy \Nto know you agreed to do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.23,0:13:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try my best.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.78,0:13:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.90,0:13:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.70,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.47,0:14:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, speak to the head girl and ask her to rearrange \Nthe program so that our play comes last.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.28,0:14:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.98,0:14:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll rehearse at once! {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.33,0:14:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get the costumes!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.50,0:14:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The script!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.10,0:14:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the props!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.94,0:14:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been changes to the program.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.62,0:14:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to unforeseen circumstances, the Romeo and Juliet play, which was supposed to be first,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.79,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will now be the final performance of the night. \NThank you for understanding.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.56,0:14:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,O Romeo, Romeo,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.03,0:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,wherefore art thou Romeo?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.27,0:14:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Deny thy father and refuse thy name...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.68,0:14:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, if thou...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.21,0:14:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, if thou wilt not, b-be...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.26,0:14:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Be but sworn my love.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.55,0:14:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.36,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.58,0:14:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.92,0:14:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.20,0:14:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it really is impossible for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.22,0:14:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just gonna ruin the play for everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.13,0:14:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.20,0:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.64,0:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Vera?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.00,0:15:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the bones are intact; \Nshe just got a sprain—a bad one.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.71,0:15:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.11,0:15:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, Miss Kennedy told me what happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.71,0:15:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be a prompter for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.85,0:15:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.92,0:15:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I mess up...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.82,0:15:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t matter! {At the very least, }We can all attest that you’ve been \Ngiving your very best despite all the odds.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.69,0:15:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Let’s just enjoy ourselves and give it our all, come what may! {?????????? nc what's that inautte}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.58,0:15:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Sheila. Let's try our best, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.20,0:15:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Sheila?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.93,0:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.73,0:15:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.83,0:15:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With Vera's help!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.23,0:15:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure! Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.95,0:15:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.40,0:15:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It suits you just right!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.82,0:16:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, it was meant to be worn by Vera.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.29,0:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.60,0:16:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who must apologize \Nfor letting everyone down like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.93,0:16:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In truth, I was jealous of Vera.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.20,0:16:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to play Juliet myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.90,0:16:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never imagined \Nit would turn out like this... {??? lit: but in this form, to think I'd have to do it - think she means "i never wanted to do it because vera injured herself"}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.64,0:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila I'm happy that you agreed to understudy me. I mean it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.78,0:16:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The first half’s over, and everyone’s heading to the cafeteria{ for the interval}. Want to come?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.92,0:16:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel like eating right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.99,0:16:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to rehearse!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.49,0:16:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll help! {lit: we're with you}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.42,0:16:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.30,0:16:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.52,0:16:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bring sandwiches for everyone. Wait here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.94,0:16:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.30,0:16:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you madly excited too?  \NI feel unstoppable right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.37,0:16:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.17,0:16:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, no time to waste. \NLet's do one more.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.78,0:16:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see Hilary and the others from her form.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.81,0:16:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They must still be rehearsing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.25,0:16:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're awfully agitated. {lit: all desperate}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.74,0:17:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be starved afterwards, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.95,0:17:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please set their meals aside for later.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.72,0:17:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.56,0:17:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.86,0:17:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.60,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.10,0:17:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's a good dog? \NBinks, I gotta run now, so see you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.12,0:17:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She's almost about done.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.43,0:17:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready. {/it's almost time}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.09,0:17:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good Lord...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.90,0:17:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all set? {lit: prepare to appear on the scene}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.44,0:17:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.61,0:17:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's torn!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.78,0:17:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t worry, we can fasten it with a safety pin.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.10,0:18:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, tell Doris to buy us some time. {lit: tell doris to extend}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.08,0:18:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.76,0:18:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.80,0:18:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done.{/fixed it}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.11,0:18:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.28,0:18:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We present to you today a sad story of love \Nbetween young Romeo and Juliet. {sounds like a quote from the orig too but i can't find it}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.63,0:18:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In fair Verona our scene is set,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.66,0:18:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where an ancient grudge has bound the noble families \Nof Montague and Capulet in endless strife.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.83,0:18:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let us look at the sacrifice of love
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.10,0:19:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,made by two pure souls, \Nas they strive to melt the icy walls
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.17,0:19:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that separate the two families. {uncertain tbh, never read/seen romeo and juliet}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.17,0:19:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the selfless tears \Nof the unfortunate couple. {?? tanuke = offering to a deity or someone's spirit}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.12,0:19:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He jests at scars that never felt a wound.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.09,0:19:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But soft, what light through yonder window breaks?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.70,0:19:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the East, and Juliet is the sun.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.97,0:19:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Arise, fair sun,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.17,0:19:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and kill the envious moon!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.41,0:19:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,O Romeo, Romeo, wherefore art thou Romeo?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.68,0:19:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Deny thy father and refuse thy name...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.04,0:19:49.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,Looking good, Sheila. {/keep it up}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.39,0:19:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, if thou wilt not, be but sworn my love,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.79,0:19:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll no longer be a Capulet.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.10,0:20:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I hear more, or shall I speak at this?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.54,0:20:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,O churl, thee drunk it all, my love? {seems they adapted the play here, in the book it's significantly better so I'm trying to work something up from what's said in japanese but writing in old english really isn't my strong suit (or modern enlgish for that matter)}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.08,0:20:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Haply some poison yet doth hang on thy lips.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.01,0:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough to make me die with a restorative.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.42,0:20:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thy lips are warm still!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.62,0:20:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thy lips are warm still...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.56,0:20:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead, boy! Which way?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.43,0:20:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yea, noise? {lit: is that a person's voice?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.57,0:20:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be brief.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.77,0:20:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,O, happy dagger, {lit: happy}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.04,0:20:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This body is thy new sheath.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.74,0:20:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My Romeo... My Romeo!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.75,0:20:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There rust, and let me die.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.19,0:21:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Some shall be pardoned,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.48,0:21:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and some punished.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.60,0:21:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For never was a story of more woe Than this of Juliet and her Romeo.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.90,0:21:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.48,0:21:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, you were incredible!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.79,0:21:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done! You got us through this crisis!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.75,0:21:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.29,0:21:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, you did great.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.53,0:21:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for a curtain call.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.53,0:21:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.83,0:21:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Sheila Naylor saved us \Nin our hour of need by urgently stepping in
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.17,0:21:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for Vera Johns, the actress playing Juliet, who was injured.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.17,0:21:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give another \Nround of applause to Sheila
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.54,0:21:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and her classmates \Nfor their outstanding performance.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.93,0:21:59.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sheila, you were the best.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.58,0:22:02.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,Everyone... Everyone was amazing.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.09,0:22:06.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,So much has happened these past few days. \NThe theatre is wonderful! {/acting}{???}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.86,0:22:10.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've never felt so connected to everyone before.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.53,0:22:12.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,Friendship is wonderful! {lit: friends are the best; fighting the urge to write in "friendship is magic"}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.46,0:22:16.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'll ever forget this day.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.85,0:23:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, we're in trouble!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.35,0:23:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.60,0:23:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Miss Kennedy \Nwill have to leave St. Clare's. {lit: will be driven out}{they're reusing the same animation, lol, i wonder if the whole episode is like that, the first book ends here so maybe they were improvising from this point on?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.65,0:23:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.39,0:23:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The history teacher, Miss Lewis, who’s been on sick leave for a long time,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.63,0:23:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming back, so Miss Kennedy \Nwill have to step down!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.86,0:23:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.73,0:23:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, I've decided not to attend her final class.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.63,0:23:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll probably burst into tears!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.94,0:23:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! I won't be able to live \Nwithout seeing Old Kenny!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.49,0:23:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.97,0:24:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Goodbye, Miss Kennedy." {さようならケネディ先生}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.36,0:24:03.86,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 13 \NGoodbye, Miss Kennedy {さようならケネディ先生}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.84,0:24:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
